Constructors:
help us create the objects from the classes in a more secure and neat. We can also put any piece of code that we want
to execute when the object of a class is created.
Why should we use constructors?
1. they help us write more secure classes
2. cleaner code
3. more control over the values that we can assign to the instance fields
Syntax:
1. no return type not even void
2. usually public access modifier
3.same name as class name
4.parameters
5.body of the constructor
Rules:


